</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1476,1528]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">
<taxonomicName box="[151,323,1476,1498]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pteroplatytrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,323,1476,1498]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Pteroplatytrygon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subgenus of 
<taxonomicName box="[484,573,1477,1498]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[484,573,1477,1498]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Dasyatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) Fowler, 1910:474. 
<typeStatus box="[796,846,1477,1498]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Bonaparte, 1832" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1832" box="[945,1303,1476,1498]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Trygon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis box="[945,1115,1476,1498]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Trygon violacea</emphasis>
Bonaparte, 1832
</taxonomicName>
; by original designation and also monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="356" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1572,2030]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1572,1597]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Definition</emphasis>
. Medium-sized dasyatid (adults to 
<quantity box="[684,756,1574,1598]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" unit="cm" value="80.0">80 cm</quantity>
DW) characterised by the following: very robust, broadly cone-shaped disc with pectoral-fin apex angular; snout short and rounded (1.1â€“1.3 times combined orbit and spiracle length); eye very small and sunken; nasal curtain skirt shaped; mouth very narrow, with numerous oral papillae; tail moderately elongate (length&gt;2 times DW), rather broad-based and depressed anteriorly, very strongly tapered at caudal sting then becoming filamentous; pelvic fins large, protruding well beyond disc, with long inner margins; dorsal fold rudimentary or absent; ventral fold low with a long base; caudal sting moderately well back on tail (distance from pectoral-fin insertion to caudal-sting base ~1.6 times interspiracular width); dense median row of small thorns and small denticles extending from nape onto tail; skin otherwise smooth or with sparse denticles; denticle band and scapular thorns absent; dorsal and ventral surfaces similarly plain and dark; marine, cosmopolitan.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1572,2030]" box="[199,640,1932,1958]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1932,1957]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Species</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bonaparte, 1832" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1832" box="[300,636,1933,1958]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Trygon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis box="[300,422,1933,1958]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">P. violacea</emphasis>
(Bonaparte, 1832)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="357" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1572,2030]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="357" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1969,1993]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Remarks</emphasis>
. Frequently assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[643,741,1970,1993]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[643,741,1970,1993]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Dasyatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Krefft" box="[834,1168,1969,1994]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" refString="Krefft, G. &amp; Stehmann, M. F. W. (1973) Dasyatidae. In: Hureau, J. - C. &amp; Monod, T. (Eds.), Check-list of the Fishes of the North- Eastern Atlantic and of the Mediterranean. CLOFNAM. Unesco, Paris, pp. 70 - 73." type="book chapter" year="1973">Krefft &amp; Stehmann, 1973</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rosenberger" box="[1195,1421,1969,1994]" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" refString="Rosenberger, L. J. (2001) Pectoral fin locomotion in batoid fishes: undulation versus oscillation. Journal of Experimental Biology, 204, 379 - 394." type="journal article" year="2001">Rosenberger, 2001</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Bonaparte, 1832" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1832" box="[151,657,2005,2030]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Pteroplatytrygon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="356" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="violacea">
<emphasis box="[151,444,2005,2030]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="356">Pteroplatytrygon violacea</emphasis>
(Bonaparte, 1832)
</taxonomicName>
is a pelagic stingray with a body shape and coloration that is unique within the family. Molecular data suggest it is not monophyletic with newly defined 
<taxonomicName box="[1166,1264,153,176]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1166,1264,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Dasyatis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but might be monophyletic when assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[514,648,188,213]" class="Elasmobranchii" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="357" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[514,648,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Bathytoshia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[664,730,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dasyatidae (subfamily Dasyatinae). Topology and branch lengths resulting from a constrained Maximum Likelihood analysis of aligned NADH 2 sequence data using the GTR + I + G model. Topological constraints were derived from an unpublished ML analysis of whole mitochondrial genomes for a representative subset of the taxa (unpublished). Members of the Neotrygoninae were used as outgroups. Names shown at branch tips are those currently in use. Revised generic names proposed are shown to the right." pageId="12" pageNumber="357">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). To avoid creating further confusion, this monotypic genus is retained provisionally pending more thorough morphological and molecular investigations.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
